<br>
Most of the guilds on the server have an unwritten understanding that you respect that other guilds exist on the server, and will discuss and work out issues of who gets to kill a mob that's been contested.   As a result, while there will always be clerics disappointed if they don't get their epic part from Rage, it generally doesn't become a guild vs. guild war once it's been discussed.  <br>
<br>
On the other hand, those guilds who refuse to discuss issues with other guilds, and play KS games end up being on the &quot;most hated&quot; list of many players.<br>
<br>
So, for those in guilds that arn't based in North America and who feel that there is unfair treatment, you may want to try having an officer who's fluent in the English language talk to those in other guilds if there even SEEMS to be a chance of there being a conflict between guilds.  I say English because EQ, no matter how many play from countries other than the USA, it IS a game that's based in the USA.  If the game was made in Taiwan, then those in the USA should expect that they would need to learn Taiwanese in order to properly fit in.  It's just common sense.<br>
