<br>
1. You may not steal kills.<br>
<br>
Kill Stealing is defined as the killing of an NPC for any reason that is already fighting <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> or pursuing another player</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> or group that is prepared to engage that same NPC without that group's specific permission.<br>
<br>
The intent of this rule is discourage and make note of habitual Kill Stealers, not to punish those who honestly try to work together or those who make an honest mistake. Its enforcement by the EverQuest Customer Service Staff will reflect this philosophy.<br>
<br>
<br>
Korwynn wrote:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> It's pretty simple actually. 3 groups come charging down the hill to human RF, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> with 1 lonely caster a few steps ahead. That one caster drew proximity agro and started running.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Ran around a bit with 3 groups chasing until I hit him with holy might (first anything done to him). Human dies pretty quick...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->According to the above PnP rule you just admitted that you KSed the caster who got aggro.<br>
<br>
<br>
Seeb wrote:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> engaging the mob makes it your mob not aggroing it<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Wrong.<br>
<br>
<br>
Ironfang wrote:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Aggro on a mob only works if you have done something to &quot;damage it&quot;. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Wrong.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
3. You must comply with arbitration for contested spawns.<br>
<br>
There are cases where two or more groups wish to kill the same NPC or hunt in the same area. In these cases, the groups are required to compromise. <br>
<br>
If an equitable compromise cannot be reached between the players prior to EverQuest Customer Service Staff involvement, the EQCSR will mandate a compromise. Any such compromise is final and not open to debate. Refusing to abide by these terms will be considered disruption and may result in disciplinary action. <br>
<br>
It is therefore strongly suggested that the groups make every attempt to reach a compromise that they can live with prior to involving an EQCSR, who may mandate a compromise that does not suit you to the extent that a player-devised compromise would.<br>
<br>
Note: A &quot;group&quot; in this case is defined as a party of one or more characters that are united in a common belief or goal and are capable of completing that goal.<br>
<br>
<br>
Targonis wrote:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Most of the guilds on the server have an unwritten understanding that you respect that other guilds exist on the server, and will discuss and work out issues of who gets to kill a mob that's been contested.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Did you try to talk to them? Or were you just prejudiced and assumed that since those people don't speak english too well they cannot be reasoned with?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
