<br>
1.  While individuals may wonder why we would bother compromising with a TW guild in any given situation, TFS DOES bother and seeks discussion to compromise with any guild.  There's always that few moments of internal discussion &quot;Are we in the right&quot;, then when we feel we are, we discuss.  Ragefire as we ALL know brings out the worst in everyone, so discussion or not, many don't think right when it comes to taking him down.<br>
<br>
2.  It's easier for a few to make quick decisions than it is for many.  The decision to back off and let the KS group die isn't a top of mind thought in TFS.  Although it sure seems justifiable in this situation and would have been pretty funny, IMO it sets a bad precedence for handling situations.   <p>Scalee <BR>
